1
00:00:07,107 --> 00:00:09,776
Enemy infiltration is
at seventy percent.

2
00:00:10,276 --> 00:00:12,345
We can't hold them
off for much longer.

3
00:00:14,247 --> 00:00:16,482
Yukari Mishakuji
and Sukuna Gojo.

4
00:00:16,517 --> 00:00:19,986
Their plan's simple:
overwhelm with brute force.

5
00:00:20,020 --> 00:00:21,955
And yet it shows just
how much confidence they

6
00:00:21,955 --> 00:00:24,324
have in their own abilities.

7
00:00:24,357 --> 00:00:26,827
They're messing with us.

8
00:00:28,128 --> 00:00:31,297
Oh my, another trap
to try to stall us?

9
00:00:31,331 --> 00:00:33,534
This is really getting
quite tiresome.

10
00:00:34,134 --> 00:00:36,302
My orders are to destroy
all the traps I can in

11
00:00:36,336 --> 00:00:39,105
order to clear a route
inside for our King.

12
00:00:39,540 --> 00:00:42,308
I understand that
that's part of my duty,

13
00:00:42,308 --> 00:00:43,877
and I've accepted that.

14
00:00:43,944 --> 00:00:45,979
Caw! Duty! Duty!

15
00:00:47,981 --> 00:00:48,949
However...

16
00:00:49,883 --> 00:00:53,820
I prefer my battles
to be more beautiful!

17
00:00:55,221 --> 00:00:57,223
We'll be more than happy
to grant your wish!

18
00:01:00,901 --> 00:01:02,503
Hm?

19
00:01:04,170 --> 00:01:05,405
[growl]

20
00:01:15,315 --> 00:01:18,051
We'll give you a beautiful
send‐off! How's that?

21
00:01:18,418 --> 00:01:19,986
Phase Two of the
plan to neutralize

22
00:01:20,020 --> 00:01:22,355
JUNGLE: concentrate
our military power in

23
00:01:22,355 --> 00:01:24,490
the Cloud Hall on the
seventy‐fifth floor and

24
00:01:24,525 --> 00:01:27,493
crush the Green
clansmen one by one.

25
00:01:27,894 --> 00:01:30,163
It's all going as
planned so far, but...

26
00:01:31,698 --> 00:01:33,667
Our sensors are detecting
massive Weismann

27
00:01:33,700 --> 00:01:35,502
levels on the lower floors!

28
00:01:35,902 --> 00:01:36,937
It's in motion!

29
00:01:37,571 --> 00:01:40,040
Agh! He's here now,
The Green King!

30
00:01:42,342 --> 00:01:44,511
This is Nagare.
I'm going in.

31
00:03:18,018 --> 00:03:20,386
[laughter] It's so
good to see him up

32
00:03:20,453 --> 00:03:21,988
and running again!

33
00:03:22,022 --> 00:03:23,990
It's been nine years since
he fought the Gold King,

34
00:03:24,024 --> 00:03:25,526
Daikaku Kokujoji.

35
00:03:26,226 --> 00:03:29,062
And it's been over a decade
since the Kagutsu Incident.

36
00:03:29,395 --> 00:03:31,131
We've been forced to
hide in the shadows

37
00:03:31,164 --> 00:03:32,566
for practically ages.

38
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:35,468
I mean really, that
stubborn old fart

39
00:03:35,502 --> 00:03:37,370
just wouldn't die!

40
00:03:39,239 --> 00:03:40,406
[sigh]

41
00:03:40,574 --> 00:03:43,744
But now Kokujoji's
finally gone.

42
00:03:43,810 --> 00:03:46,680
And that means there's
no one left in this

43
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:49,015
entire world that
can stop you when

44
00:03:49,049 --> 00:03:51,652
you're at full
power, Nagare.

45
00:03:52,853 --> 00:03:55,756
That's it, Nagare!
Run wild all you want!

46
00:03:56,189 --> 00:03:59,092
Mr. Iwa's here to get your
back, so go right on ahead

47
00:03:59,159 --> 00:04:00,701
and have an absolute blast!

48
00:04:01,201 --> 00:04:02,235
[laughter]

49
00:04:03,436 --> 00:04:04,370
[gasp]

50
00:04:05,171 --> 00:04:07,608
Holy crap! That
was way too close!

51
00:04:09,710 --> 00:04:12,045
What's that noise?!
Is it more of them?!

52
00:04:12,546 --> 00:04:15,616
Hey! C'mon, you Blues! Hurry
up and get into position!

53
00:04:16,550 --> 00:04:18,785
Oh my, you're here
already, are you?

54
00:04:20,186 --> 00:04:21,387
Here already?

55
00:04:21,555 --> 00:04:23,223
You don't mean!

56
00:04:23,256 --> 00:04:24,625
Yes, that's right.

57
00:04:25,425 --> 00:04:26,560
He's coming...

58
00:04:27,127 --> 00:04:27,794
[gasp]

59
00:04:28,729 --> 00:04:32,065
How very unfortunate.
Truly unfortunate.

60
00:04:32,432 --> 00:04:34,400
And just when things
were finally starting to

61
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:36,135
become interesting.

62
00:04:36,202 --> 00:04:38,404
But now it's all
over. Oh, well.

63
00:04:38,638 --> 00:04:40,073
Over! It's over!

64
00:04:40,574 --> 00:04:42,408
What do you mean, over?

65
00:04:42,609 --> 00:04:44,210
It's the Green King!

66
00:04:44,244 --> 00:04:46,246
I didn't expect him so soon.

67
00:04:46,647 --> 00:04:48,281
Hey, what's the matter?!

68
00:04:48,314 --> 00:04:49,716
Don't act like cowards!

