00:14:20,286 --> 00:14:22,656
Hello, Red King,
Anna Kushina.

257
00:14:23,223 --> 00:14:26,693
I must ask you to forgive my
rude entrance back there.

258
00:14:26,727 --> 00:14:27,828
I'm in a hurry.

259
00:14:28,194 --> 00:14:29,029
Apologies.

260
00:14:29,863 --> 00:14:31,965
Enough, Green
King, Nagare Hisui.

261
00:14:32,332 --> 00:14:34,835
Just give it up. We
cannot and will not

262
00:14:34,835 --> 00:14:35,869
let you have it.

263
00:14:36,870 --> 00:14:39,172
The Slate is not merely
your toy to play with.

264
00:14:39,973 --> 00:14:42,876
You're right. It's not my
toy. I'm in complete

265
00:14:42,909 --> 00:14:44,410
agreement with you on that.

266
00:14:45,712 --> 00:14:47,981
A world where players are
granted powers that far

267
00:14:48,014 --> 00:14:50,383
exceed the limits of
humankind and compete

268
00:14:50,416 --> 00:14:51,685
to reach the top.

269
00:14:52,352 --> 00:14:54,054
The Dresden Slate
is a catalyst that

270
00:14:54,087 --> 00:14:55,856
serves that purpose.

271
00:14:55,889 --> 00:14:59,092
Which means it doesn't
belong to me alone.

272
00:14:59,159 --> 00:15:00,867
It belongs to everyone.

273
00:15:01,234 --> 00:15:02,503
You must stop.

274
00:15:02,536 --> 00:15:05,038
No, I will not stop,
nor can I be stopped.

275
00:15:06,039 --> 00:15:08,241
Watch, Anna Kushina,
I'm now going to

276
00:15:08,274 --> 00:15:10,043
achieve my objective.

277
00:15:10,443 --> 00:15:11,444
Stop! Now!

278
00:15:26,527 --> 00:15:28,895
You've only been a King
for a very short time

279
00:15:28,929 --> 00:15:31,131
and yet you seem to
have great control

280
00:15:31,197 --> 00:15:32,398
over your power.

281
00:15:32,899 --> 00:15:33,967
I'm impressed.

282
00:15:35,135 --> 00:15:37,437
You do not understand the
true meaning of this power.

283
00:15:38,071 --> 00:15:41,241
Power by itself has
no intrinsic meaning.

284
00:15:41,241 --> 00:15:44,044
It is the people who
wield power that are the

285
00:15:44,077 --> 00:15:45,879
ones who provide it meaning.

286
00:15:46,146 --> 00:15:47,213
That's not true!

287
00:15:48,882 --> 00:15:51,417
Fine, then. Since we've
confirmed that our opinions

288
00:15:51,417 --> 00:15:53,086
are at odds with each other.

289
00:15:53,554 --> 00:15:56,122
Now the games shall begin!

290
00:16:03,937 --> 00:16:05,105
[chuckle]

291
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:15,015
A lightning beast?!

292
00:16:19,853 --> 00:16:22,789
Anna and Nagare Hisui
are battling each other.

293
00:16:23,256 --> 00:16:24,357
Look! There!

294
00:16:41,107 --> 00:16:42,208
I've arrived at last!

295
00:16:43,043 --> 00:16:44,010
My goal!

296
00:16:45,211 --> 00:16:47,447
Sorry, no goal just yet.

297
00:17:02,536 --> 00:17:04,905
It's time! He's
used up his power.

298
00:17:12,212 --> 00:17:14,147
Anna! Mr. Munakata!

299
00:17:23,489 --> 00:17:27,360
So? How was it, Nagare
Hisui? Did you enjoy your

300
00:17:27,393 --> 00:17:29,229
pointless little rampage?

301
00:17:29,495 --> 00:17:32,032
There's no sense or
order to your actions.

302
00:17:32,065 --> 00:17:33,600
In your frenzy of
destruction, you were

303
00:17:33,667 --> 00:17:36,369
essentially like an animal.

304
00:17:36,537 --> 00:17:41,207
Oh, it was almost unbearably
fun, Reisi Munakata.

305
00:17:41,341 --> 00:17:44,545
You do realize that humans
are animals, too, right?

306
00:17:44,545 --> 00:17:47,447
We're all just individual
creatures that happen to be

307
00:17:47,514 --> 00:17:49,583
different from each other.

308
00:17:49,616 --> 00:17:53,053
Don't you agree with
that, Miyabi Ameno?

309
00:17:53,687 --> 00:17:55,021
You mean me?!

310
00:17:56,557 --> 00:17:58,892
But I'm Neko!

311
00:17:59,025 --> 00:17:59,926
Miyabi Ameno...

312
00:18:00,561 --> 00:18:02,569
Even with SCEPTER 4's
resources, we couldn't

313
00:18:02,603 --> 00:18:04,705
identify that girl.

314
00:18:04,738 --> 00:18:07,240
So that is her real
name, then, is it?

315
00:18:07,273 --> 00:18:09,643
Although, wouldn't you
say that she's a bit

316
00:18:09,710 --> 00:18:12,979
too unique to use as an
example of what ordinary,

317
00:18:13,046 --> 00:18:14,648
everyday humans are like?

318
00:18:15,481 --> 00:18:17,918
You believe that
because you're a fool.

319
00:18:18,619 --> 00:18:20,554
She and I are both the same...

320
00:18:21,087 --> 00:18:23,256
We can define ourselves
without being limited

321
00:18:23,289 --> 00:18:25,592
by whatever human
qualities just happen

322
00:18:25,626 --> 00:18:27,060
to be forced upon us.

323
00:18:28,261 --> 00:18:30,296
It's possession of that free
spirit that throws open the

324
00:18:30,330 --> 00:18:32,432
doors of human possibility.

325
00:18:32,465 --> 00:18:35,636
And now, I the one nearest
that free‐spirited ideal,

326
00:18:35,669 --> 00:18:38,438
have come here to
receive the Slate.

327
00:18:39,072 --> 00:18:40,574
Are you saying you're
the most suitable

328
00:18:40,607 --> 00:18:42,609
to manage the Slate?

329
00:18:42,609 --> 00:18:46,513
The amount of arrogance you
show is just astounding.

330
00:18:47,480 --> 00:18:49,950
Don't misunderstand
me, Reisi Munakata.

331
00:18:50,517 --> 00:18:52,586
Really, it's completely
impossible for anyone

332
00:18:52,619 --> 00:18:55,288
to be "suitable" to
manage the Dresden Slate.

333
00:18:56,289 --> 00:18:59,025
It's the wellspring of
possibilities, and to think

334
00:18:59,092 --> 00:19:02,035
one can arbitrarily
control it shows a total

335
00:19:02,102 --> 00:19:04,470
lack of understanding
of its true nature.

336
00:19:05,105 --> 00:19:06,773
The whole idea's absurd.

337
00:19:06,807 --> 00:19:09,643
Oh, I see. Don't try
to manage the power,

338
00:19:09,676 --> 00:19:11,311
merely release it.

339
00:19:12,212 --> 00:19:14,548
Creating unbridled chaos is
the meaning of the Slate's

340
00:19:14,615 --> 00:19:16,382
existence, is that right?

341
00:19:17,317 --> 00:19:18,519
Is that what you're saying?

342
00:19:20,020 --> 00:19:21,622
No, there is no meaning.

343
00:19:22,155 --> 00:19:25,125
Those who possess power
simply use it in any way

344
00:19:25,158 --> 00:19:26,660
that they want, that's all.

345
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:30,196
But look, your power is
exhausted. This situation

346
00:19:30,230 --> 00:19:32,065
you've found yourself in.

347
00:19:32,132 --> 00:19:34,000
How do you explain that?

348
00:19:37,504 --> 00:19:41,675
Nagare Hisui, you are
already a dead man.

349
00:19:41,675 --> 00:19:43,744
According to the
Silver King's data, you

350
00:19:43,810 --> 00:19:46,647
lost your heart during
the Kagutsu Incident.

351
00:19:46,680 --> 00:19:49,683
Your power alone is
sustaining your existence,

352
00:19:49,716 --> 00:19:51,718
and barely at that.

353
00:19:51,752 --> 00:19:54,054
That explains how you're
able to manipulate your

354
00:19:54,087 --> 00:19:56,557
physical capabilities
to such an extreme.

355
00:19:57,524 --> 00:20:00,661
However, once your power
has become all used up

356
00:20:00,694 --> 00:20:03,637
you're like a toy with a
dead battery inside of it.

357
00:20:04,470 --> 00:20:07,541
Or rather, your original
self which is to say,

358
00:20:07,608 --> 00:20:09,009
nothing but a corpse.

359
00:20:10,143 --> 00:20:12,212
I hardly think that you're
qualified to battle me in

360
00:20:12,278 --> 00:20:14,981
order to determine
who has the right to

361
00:20:15,015 --> 00:20:16,449
possess the Slate.

362
00:20:16,683 --> 00:20:19,185
[chuckle] Perhaps
you're right.

363
00:20:19,219 --> 00:20:21,454
But then, I'm not the
one you're going to

364
00:20:21,487 --> 00:20:23,056
be doing battle against.

365
00:20:23,557 --> 00:20:26,192
"He" will be arriving
here shortly using the

366
00:20:26,226 --> 00:20:29,630
path I've cleared.
"He" is my trump card.

367
00:20:31,164 --> 00:20:31,832
Come on!

368
00:20:32,699 --> 00:20:34,735
Anna our King!
Is in danger!

369
00:20:34,801 --> 00:20:37,337
Ya hear?! Show
some guts, bastards!

370
00:20:37,370 --> 00:20:38,304
Right!

371
00:20:39,339 --> 00:20:41,307
[chuckle] At times like
these, it sure is good to

372
00:20:41,341 --> 00:20:42,475
have Yata around!

373
00:20:43,476 --> 00:20:44,310
Huh?!

374
00:20:45,178 --> 00:20:48,048
Hey, this fog,
Where'd it come from?

375
00:20:49,249 --> 00:20:50,684
[gasps]

376
00:20:50,684 --> 00:20:52,318
Everyone! Be careful!

377
00:20:53,654 --> 00:20:56,557
Yata! Kamamoto! Seri!

378
00:21:15,415 --> 00:21:17,050
Who are you?!

379
00:21:25,291 --> 00:21:26,593
What the hell was that?

380
00:21:27,728 --> 00:21:29,429
[gasp] Anna!

381
00:21:29,696 --> 00:21:31,565
An unknown sanctum just
appeared inside the tower!

382
00:21:31,765 --> 00:21:33,534
It's another King, sir!

383
00:21:33,734 --> 00:21:35,401
[gasp] What?!

384
00:21:36,136 --> 00:21:39,439
Vertical over. A Sword of
Damocles is manifesting!

385
00:21:42,208 --> 00:21:44,110
Impossible! Another King?!

386
00:22:02,135 --> 00:22:03,103
Mr. Munakata!

387
00:22:03,570 --> 00:22:06,439
Yes, I see. Nagare Hisui's
reckless actions and

388
00:22:06,472 --> 00:22:09,643
surprising confidence
can be explained by the

389
00:22:09,676 --> 00:22:12,813
fact that you were the
one behind this all along.

390
00:22:15,582 --> 00:22:17,618
You, who were said
to have died during

391
00:22:17,651 --> 00:22:19,653
the Kagutsu Incident.

392
00:22:19,686 --> 00:22:22,422
The Sixth King!
The Gray King!

393
00:22:23,256 --> 00:22:25,792
Whoa, hold on. Just
wait a second, Munakata.

394
00:22:26,627 --> 00:22:29,362
The beginning is crucial in
human relationships.

395
00:22:29,796 --> 00:22:31,632
So I just have one
thing to say first.

396
00:22:32,465 --> 00:22:36,136
If you wanna talk
to me, call me Mr. Iwa!

397
00:24:09,743 --> 00:24:11,044
The final sword
that remained

398
00:24:11,077 --> 00:24:13,614
hidden till now, Gray.

399
00:24:14,447 --> 00:24:18,451
Next time on K RETURN OF
KINGS, Episode 8 "Kaput."

400
00:24:19,085 --> 00:24:22,923
You are a coward, but
also a very tragic figure.

